Kristen King, MPH

About Me

I am a Data Analyst in the Nephrology Division at Columbia University Medical Center with a background in Epidemiology and Applied Biostatistics. I am also currently a part-time MA student in the Department of Biomedical Informatics. More details on my academic and professional experience can be found on my Experience Page.

I work with the Columbia University Renal Epidemiology (CURE) group performing observational research on kidney transplantation using national transplant registry data. My research interests include disparities in access to kidney transplantation and clinical decision support in organ allocation and organ offer acceptance.
